{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/ClassicalMechanics/Lagrangian/TotalDerivativeEquivalence.html#ClassicalMechanics.Lagrangian.isTotalTimeDerivativeVelocity\"><span class=\"name\">ClassicalMechanics</span>.<span class=\"name\">Lagrangian</span>.<span class=\"name\">isTotalTimeDerivativeVelocity</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">δL</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/PiL2.html#EuclideanSpace\">EuclideanSpace</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span>)</span></span> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hδL0</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">δL</span> <span class=\"fn\">0</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/ClassicalMechanics/Lagrangian/TotalDerivativeEquivalence.html#ClassicalMechanics.Lagrangian.IsTotalTimeDerivative\">IsTotalTimeDerivative</a> <span class=\"fn\">fun (<span class=\"fn\">x</span> <span class=\"fn\">v</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/PiL2.html#EuclideanSpace\">EuclideanSpace</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span>)</span></span>) (<span class=\"fn\">x_1</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">δL</span> <span class=\"fn\">v</span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">∃ (<span class=\"fn\">g</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/PiL2.html#EuclideanSpace\">EuclideanSpace</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span>)</span></span>), <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">v</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/PiL2.html#EuclideanSpace\">EuclideanSpace</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span>)</span></span>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">δL</span> <span class=\"fn\">v</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Defs.html#Inner.inner\">inner</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">g</span> <span class=\"fn\">v</span></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A velocity-only function that is a total time derivative must be linear in velocity.\n\nIf δL depends only on velocity and equals d/dt F(r, t) for some F,\nthen δL(v) = ⟨g, v⟩ for some constant vector g.\n\nThis characterization comes from the requirement that:\n- d/dt F(r, t) = ∂F/∂t + ⟨∇F, ṙ⟩ = ∂F/∂t + ⟨∇F, v⟩\n- For the result to be independent of r and t, we need ∇F = g (constant) and ∂F/∂t = 0\n- Thus δL(v) = ⟨g, v⟩\n\nWLOG, we assume `δL 0 = 0` since constants are total derivatives (c = d/dt(c·t))\nand can be absorbed without affecting the equations of motion. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/ClassicalMechanics/Lagrangian/TotalDerivativeEquivalence.html#ClassicalMechanics.Lagrangian.isTotalTimeDerivativeVelocity","kind":"theorem","line":88,"name":"ClassicalMechanics.Lagrangian.isTotalTimeDerivativeVelocity","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L88-L161"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/ClassicalMechanics/Lagrangian/TotalDerivativeEquivalence.html#ClassicalMechanics.Lagrangian.IsTotalTimeDerivative\"><span class=\"name\">ClassicalMechanics</span>.<span class=\"name\">Lagrangian</span>.<span class=\"name\">IsTotalTimeDerivative</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">δL</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/PiL2.html#EuclideanSpace\">EuclideanSpace</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span>)</span></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/PiL2.html#EuclideanSpace\">EuclideanSpace</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span>)</span></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A function δL(r, v, t) is a total time derivative if it can be written as d/dt F(r, t)\nfor some function F that depends on position and time but not velocity.\n\nMathematically: δL(r, v, t) = fderiv ℝ F (r, t) (v, 1)\n\nBy the chain rule, this equals ∂F/∂t(r, t) + ⟨∇ᵣF(r, t), v⟩.\n\nThis is the most general form of Lagrangian equivalence under total derivatives.\nThe key point is that F must be independent of velocity. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/ClassicalMechanics/Lagrangian/TotalDerivativeEquivalence.html#ClassicalMechanics.Lagrangian.IsTotalTimeDerivative","kind":"def","line":66,"name":"ClassicalMechanics.Lagrangian.IsTotalTimeDerivative","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L66-L78"}}],"imports":["Init","PhysLean.Mathematics.VariationalCalculus.HasVarGradient"],"instances":[],"name":"PhysLean.ClassicalMechanics.Lagrangian.TotalDerivativeEquivalence"}